Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.36,0:00:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if we think about Jesus’ words
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.44,0:00:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,in today’s text,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.15,0:00:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,“give us today our bread for this day,”
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.49,0:00:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,there’s really indirect counsel
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.53,0:00:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,against materialism.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.66,0:00:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,See, Jesus didn’t say to pray
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.75,0:00:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,for our daily meat
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.25,0:00:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,or some other luxury food item.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.63,0:00:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn’t even say that we should pray\Nfor a month’s supply of bread
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.55,0:00:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,but to ‘pray for and be content\Nwith our bread for the day.’
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.47,0:00:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But, as we know,\Na sizable number of Jehovah’s people today
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.31,0:00:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,are being distracted by materialism.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.48,0:00:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So since this is not an imagined
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.32,0:00:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,but a real danger to Jehovah’s people,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.74,0:00:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s discuss the theme
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.12,0:00:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,“Beware of the Power of Materialism.”
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.91,0:00:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I recall the story\Nof a sister and her two sons
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.83,0:01:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,who were exiled to Siberia.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.42,0:01:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, they were very poor.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.43,0:01:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact,\Nthey were so poor that at times
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.47,0:01:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,they had to literally eat\Nthe bark off trees to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.48,0:01:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But they were happy\Nbecause they were all in the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.77,0:01:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But years passed,\Nand the three of them had an opportunity
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.40,0:01:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to immigrate to the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.28,0:01:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The two sons got excellent jobs\N—high paying jobs as machinists—
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.28,0:01:31.99,Default,,0,0,0,,but in their material prosperity,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.99,0:01:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,both sons fell out of the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.87,0:01:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The sister tearfully remarked,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.29,0:01:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“I would rather be back in Siberia
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.46,0:01:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“eating the bark off trees to survive
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.72,0:01:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,but with my two sons still in the truth.”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.35,0:01:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, numerous other experiences\Ncould be related
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.89,0:01:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that illustrate the power of materialism.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.44,0:01:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, it may well be
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.69,0:01:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that Satan’s most effective trap
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.86,0:02:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,against Jehovah’s people in these last days
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.19,0:02:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is materialism.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.24,0:02:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, you might be thinking,\N‘Well, isn’t sexual immorality
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.95,0:02:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,by far the number one cause\Nfor disfellowshipping?’
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.75,0:02:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s true, but we don’t have figures\Nfor ones who fall away to materialism.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.34,0:02:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re not disfellowshipped.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.42,0:02:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And furthermore,\Nhow many who succumb to sexual immorality
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.43,0:02:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,were first weakened spiritually
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.81,0:02:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,by materialism?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.85,0:02:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, at least we can say that materialism
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.77,0:02:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,is one of Satan’s most effective tools,\Nor traps,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.77,0:02:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,against Jehovah’s people today.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.49,0:02:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And it’s no wonder\Nthat humans in Satan’s world
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.99,0:02:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,are bombarded\Nwith so many advertising messages
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.45,0:02:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,designed to make us want things,\Neven if we don’t need these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.29,0:02:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,There was an {\i1}{\fs16}{\fnArial}Awake!{\r}  magazine a while back
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.96,0:03:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that discussed how Americans
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.26,0:03:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,may be bombarded
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.30,0:03:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,with up to 1,600 advertising messages\Nevery day.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.26,0:03:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine that!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.27,0:03:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And none of us can feel we’re immune
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.60,0:03:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to this pressure\N—that it can’t happen to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.02,0:03:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It could happen to any of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.44,0:03:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We could slowly, gradually,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.73,0:03:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,begin to desire material things
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.82,0:03:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,—even things we don’t really need.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.45,0:03:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, that makes me think of the story
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.70,0:03:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,a circuit overseer told many years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.71,0:03:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a young teenager.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.75,0:03:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That was over 50 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.34,0:03:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He and his wife lived in a little trailer
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.42,0:03:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,they would park by the Kingdom Hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.84,0:03:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And he said in one of his talks\Nhow he bought a drill
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.22,0:03:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to do work on his trailer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.35,0:03:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But then shortly after he bought this drill,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.39,0:03:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,they came out with a reversible drill.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.64,0:03:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And he thought:\N‘Well, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.15,0:03:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,‘that would be nice\Nto have a reversible drill.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.23,0:04:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be much easier\Nto extract the drill bit out of the hole.’
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.11,0:04:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So he bought a reversible drill.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.20,0:04:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Shortly after that,\Nthey came out with a reversible drill
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.74,0:04:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that had a little light on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.08,0:04:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You’d pull the trigger,\Nand a little light would come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.08,0:04:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And he thought:\N‘You know, that would be really nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.08,0:04:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,My drill doesn’t have a little light on it.’
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.59,0:04:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He was about ready to buy this latest model,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.92,0:04:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and then he said:\N“Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.93,0:04:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,“What am I doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.93,0:04:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,How often am I going to be drilling\Nat night?”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.10,0:04:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But he told that\Nto illustrate how materialism
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.56,0:04:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,can get a hold of any of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.86,0:04:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,He was being manipulated by Satan’s system.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.32,0:04:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, here’s a question:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.32,0:04:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What Bible principles
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.33,0:04:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,can help us avoid this deadly trap,\Nmaterialism?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.29,0:04:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s discuss two.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.29,0:04:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, there are many others,\Nbut these two can really help us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.09,0:04:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s go to Micah chapter 7,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.76,0:05:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and let’s get this first Bible principle\Nthat really can help us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.51,0:05:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Micah 7:7:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.30,0:05:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“But as for me,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.64,0:05:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,“I will keep on the lookout for Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.77,0:05:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,“[now notice] I will show a waiting attitude
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.77,0:05:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,“for the God of my salvation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.28,0:05:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,My God will hear me.”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.24,0:05:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Or the footnote says:\N“I will wait patiently.”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.78,0:05:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,See, are we willing\Nto wait patiently on Jehovah?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.08,0:05:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,This certainly applies to material things.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.67,0:05:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah, in effect, is telling us today:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.21,0:05:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I’m giving you
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.30,0:05:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,‘a spiritual paradise right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.47,0:05:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Be content with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.51,0:05:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Don’t try to get your physical paradise now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.10,0:05:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll give you that later.’
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.27,0:05:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But the question is,\NAre we willing to wait on Jehovah, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.98,0:05:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Or do we, in effect,\Nrun ahead of him and try to acquire
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.48,0:05:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,physical paradisaic conditions\Nfor ourselves right now
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.16,0:06:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,at the expense of spiritual activity?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.16,0:06:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Ecclesiastes 3:1 says:
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.96,0:06:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“There is an appointed time for everything.”
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.00,0:06:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Jehovah has appointed our time
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.71,0:06:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,—especially these last days\Nof “the last days”
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.88,0:06:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,shortly before the last day\Nof this old system—
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.14,0:06:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,not as the time to seek and spend time
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.77,0:06:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,acquiring physical comforts
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.56,0:06:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,but, rather,\Nas a time to beautify this spiritual paradise
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.40,0:06:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and help others join us in this paradise.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.24,0:06:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,No wonder at 1 Peter 1:1 and 2:11
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.99,0:06:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,God’s people are described\Nas “temporary residents!”
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.83,0:06:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And it’s a real protection\Nif we think of ourselves that way:
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.17,0:06:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,temporary residents.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.17,0:06:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the illustration has been used\Nof staying in a hotel room.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.84,0:06:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you know when you’re in a hotel room,\Nyou’re a temporary resident.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.93,0:07:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You might do a few things\Nto make your stay more comfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.10,0:07:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You might rearrange the chairs;\Nyou might reposition the lamps;
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.65,0:07:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you might buy some flowers\Nand put them on the table;
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.44,0:07:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,you might spray some air freshener.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.82,0:07:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But you would never rip off the wallpaper
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.95,0:07:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and install new wallpaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.37,0:07:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You’d never rip up the carpet\Nand install new carpet or tile.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.37,0:07:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You wouldn’t buy new furniture.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.00,0:07:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You’d keep it simple
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.63,0:07:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,because you know\Nyou’re going to be checking out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.00,0:07:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, even if you ended up\Nstaying a few months in that hotel room,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.68,0:07:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,especially if you didn’t know exactly when\Nyou’re going to have to check out,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.26,0:07:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,you would still keep it simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.43,0:07:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that describes our situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.56,0:07:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re going to “check out”\Nof this old system.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.36,0:07:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re going to “check in”\Nto the new world.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.19,0:07:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We don’t know exactly when,\Nbut we know it’s soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.61,0:07:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So we keep it simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.61,0:07:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re “temporary residents.”
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.66,0:08:00.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, let’s get a second Bible principle
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.29,0:08:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,that can help us avoid materialism.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.33,0:08:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s go to Luke chapter 10.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.58,0:08:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And Jesus’ words here
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.00,0:08:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,can help us identify\Nthis second Bible principle.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.26,0:08:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,At Luke 10:42, the {\i1}{\fs16}{\fnArial}B{\r}  part,\NJesus said:
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.97,0:08:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,“For her part,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.01,0:08:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,“Mary chose the good portion,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.98,0:08:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and it will not be taken away from her.”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.98,0:08:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You notice she chose the good portion.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.02,0:08:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The footnote says the “best portion.”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.11,0:08:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we know the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.11,0:08:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Martha chose physical activity.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.99,0:08:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,She chose working in the kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.79,0:08:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Mary chose spiritual activity\N—listening to Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.17,0:08:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus correctly identified\Nwho made the best choice,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.79,0:08:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,who chose the best portion.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.80,0:08:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, similarly with us,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.97,0:08:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,when we choose\N‘storing up treasure in heaven’
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.59,0:08:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,over ‘storing up treasure on the earth,’
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.26,0:09:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,we are choosing the best portion.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.18,0:09:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,How so?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.81,0:09:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, for one thing,\Nit brings Jehovah’s blessing,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.98,0:09:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and that results in happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.65,0:09:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We all know what Proverbs 10:22 says:
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.86,0:09:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,“It is the blessing of Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.24,0:09:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,“that makes one rich,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.33,0:09:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and He adds no pain with it.”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.70,0:09:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,In contrast,\N1 Timothy 6:9, 10
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.04,0:09:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,speaks about how those who go out
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.46,0:09:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,for money or material things
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.63,0:09:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,can end up ‘stabbing themselves
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.89,0:09:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,all over with many pains.’
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.47,0:09:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, isn’t that a contrast
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.52,0:09:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,—blessing from Jehovah with no pain
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.35,0:09:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and stabbing yourself all over\Nwith many pains?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.40,0:09:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we’re choosing the best portion\Nwhen we go for spiritual, heavenly, treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.40,0:09:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, another reason is heavenly treasure
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.28,0:09:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,will result in preservation\Ninto the new world,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.66,0:09:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,if necessary by means of the resurrection.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.33,0:10:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Proverbs 11:4:
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.37,0:10:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,“Wealth will be of no benefit\Non the day of fury,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.75,0:10:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,but righteousness\Nis what will rescue from death.”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.76,0:10:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So remembering those two Bible principles\Ncan really help us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.76,0:10:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember that we are to wait on Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.44,0:10:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And he says,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.48,0:10:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,‘It’s a spiritual paradise now \Nand a physical paradise later.’
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.02,0:10:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We wait on him, and when we do that\N(that second principle),
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.40,0:10:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,we’re choosing “the best portion.”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.61,0:10:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’re going to be happy.\NWe’re going to get Jehovah’s blessings.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.49,0:10:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we do this, then, like Moses,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.74,0:10:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ll choose treasures
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.75,0:10:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,“greater than the treasures of Egypt.”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.38,0:10:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll be able to do what Jesus said
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.13,0:10:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,—to pray for and to be content\Nwith our daily bread.
